"{\n  \"text\": \"We eat too many processed foods. We eat too much cooked foods. We don't eat foods that still have the life web that was the food was grown with attached to it still. The bacteria that are eating the foods that we eat are so important to us because they help our body digest it and they give life web forces to our gut bacteria. So foods that have been processed so that they've been uh cooked and then dried out and preserved so they can exist on the shelf are dead foods. Foods that we cook are dead foods. We kill the bacteria. There's all sorts of different ways that we preserve food that destroy the bacteria, but are there's lots of great ways of preserving food, i.e. fermentation, that preserve the life force and in fact actually enhance the life force that create more bacteria that are digesting the foods for us so that we not only get help digesting them, but we also aid our life force with life forces from the outside. Dead and processed foods kill our gut. Thanks, y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" We eat too many processed foods.\",\n      \"start\": 0.0,\n      \"end\": 1.6,\n      \"duration\": 1.6,\n      \"confidence\": 0.994,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" We\",\n          \"start\": 0.0,\n          \"end\": 0.24,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.996\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" e\",\n          \"start\": 0.24,\n          \"end\": 0.32,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"at\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.48,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" to\",\n          \"start\": 0.48,\n          \"end\": 0.56,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"o\",\n          \"start\": 0.56,\n          \"end\": 0.64,\n          \"durat